Past-Tense Review
Focused heavily on past-tense recall and fixing repeated weak spots:

Nos invitaron = They invited us
Los invitamos = We invited them
Nos gustó = We liked it
No le gustó la música = She didn’t like the music
Fuimos juntos = We went together
Comenzó tarde = It started late
Ella se fue = She left
Llegué tarde el martes = I arrived late on Tuesday
Main Weak Areas
present vs past tense endings
invitan vs invitaron
gusta vs gustó
object pronouns like lo/la/le
remembering new infinitives like pedir and regresar
small grammar connectors under pressure
Main Improvements
stronger recall of weekly phrases
better restaurant conversation flow
improved past tense recognition
faster responses without notes
stronger tourism/travel vocabulary
better confidence with longer sentence structures
Overall, Day 58 was a strong review day focused on real-world Puerto Rico conversation, restaurant phrasing, and more difficult past-tense structures.
